WEBVTT

00:01.369 --> 00:05.039
[ Upbeat music plays ]

00:05.073 --> 00:15.116
♪♪

00:22.423 --> 00:29.997
♪♪

00:30.030 --> 00:31.832
-Dude, wake up!
-[ Shrieks ]

00:31.865 --> 00:33.901
-What?
-It's finally here.

00:33.934 --> 00:35.836
The most magical
day of all.

00:35.869 --> 00:38.472
What, the day where the old,
hairy man breaks into houses

00:38.506 --> 00:40.574
in the dead of night
with a bag for the children?

00:40.608 --> 00:42.243
What? No,
and for the record,

00:42.276 --> 00:44.778
that's the creepiest description
of Christmas I've ever heard.

00:44.812 --> 00:47.348
I meant today is
the day we veg out.

00:47.381 --> 00:49.350
You don't want to do
anything at all today?

00:49.383 --> 00:50.684
No, I'm on strike.

00:50.718 --> 00:53.087
It's like if the tiniest thing
happens in this town,

00:53.121 --> 00:55.556
we end up running
a gosh-darned marathon.

00:55.589 --> 00:56.590
Look at these.

00:56.624 --> 00:58.992
♪♪

00:59.026 --> 01:01.095
Fair enough.
So, what are we gonna do?

01:01.129 --> 01:05.099
Whatever happens,
we do absolutely nothing.

01:05.133 --> 01:07.668
First, we shall neither bathe
nor groom ourselves.

01:07.701 --> 01:09.002
Instead, we shall
clothe ourselves

01:09.036 --> 01:11.305
in the ceremonial robes
of the blanket toga.

01:11.339 --> 01:13.073
Then we shall open and close
the door of the fridge

01:13.107 --> 01:14.942
so many times that
we lower our standards,

01:14.975 --> 01:16.577
so many times that
we eventually settle

01:16.610 --> 01:19.380
for a feast of expired pickles,
slightly fermented orange juice,

01:19.413 --> 01:21.415
and what was once butter
but may now be cheese.

01:21.449 --> 01:24.185
If the glasses are dirty,
we shall drink out of bowls.

01:24.218 --> 01:27.020
And if the bowls are dirty,
we shall drink out of plates!

01:27.054 --> 01:29.323
We shall nest under a blanket
on the sofa for so long

01:29.357 --> 01:31.192
that when we stand up,
we will suffer vertigo

01:31.225 --> 01:33.627
and immediately
have to lie back down.

01:33.661 --> 01:36.096
And we shall continue
to do naught

01:36.130 --> 01:39.267
until we are plagued
with the guilt of laziness,

01:39.300 --> 01:42.603
and the sweat on our foreheads
has turned to grease!

01:42.636 --> 01:45.105
Then, my friend,
and only then

01:45.139 --> 01:48.376
will we have earned the right
to go to bed

01:48.409 --> 01:50.944
in our own juices.

01:50.978 --> 01:54.182
[ Breathing heavily ]

01:54.215 --> 01:56.016
All right.
So, when do we get up?

01:56.049 --> 01:58.152
When the discomfort of having
to go to the bathroom

01:58.186 --> 02:02.055
exceeds the joy
of lying in bed. Hmm.

02:02.089 --> 02:03.457
Gumball:
There. This should prevent

02:03.491 --> 02:06.194
chafing from too much sitting.
Now do my chin.

02:06.227 --> 02:08.796
Okay, but why do you
need lip balm there?

02:08.829 --> 02:10.664
'Cause TV face.

02:10.698 --> 02:13.734
'Kay, by the way, why is the TV
the wrong way around?

02:13.767 --> 02:18.005
♪♪

02:18.038 --> 02:19.540
Taking it to
the next level, huh?

02:19.573 --> 02:21.442
Yep.
The next level down.

02:21.475 --> 02:23.377
Should I bring a bucket
in case we need to,

02:23.411 --> 02:25.179
y-you know, powder our nose?

02:25.213 --> 02:29.116
[ As announcer ]
Slackies -- when you got to go,
but you don't want to leave.

02:29.149 --> 02:31.585
But what if we need
to change video game?

02:31.619 --> 02:33.454
[ Normal voice ]
Mm-hmm.

02:33.487 --> 02:36.924
♪♪

02:36.957 --> 02:39.193
Wow, I guess you really
thought of everything.

02:39.227 --> 02:40.894
But what if someone
rings the doorbell?

02:40.928 --> 02:42.296
Oh, I've got a life hack
for that, as well.

02:42.330 --> 02:43.897
-What?
-I don't answer it.

02:43.931 --> 02:46.267
Come on, let's get
into position.

02:46.300 --> 02:48.536
-[ Clears throat ]
-Oh, sorry.

02:48.569 --> 02:49.703
[ Grumbles ]

02:49.737 --> 02:51.038
[ Both sigh ]

02:51.071 --> 02:53.541
[ Telephone rings ]
Aw, man, the phone!

02:53.574 --> 02:55.108
-What do we do?
-Nothing.

02:55.142 --> 02:56.777
It's really annoying,
though.

02:56.810 --> 02:58.912
So the phone's ringing.
Big deal.

02:58.946 --> 03:01.215
We just wait until
our brains tune it out.

03:01.249 --> 03:03.751
[ High-pitched whining ]

03:03.784 --> 03:05.219
See, it just went awa--

03:05.253 --> 03:06.920
This is NASA!
You need to get out!
[ Siren wailing ]

03:06.954 --> 03:09.122
There's a meteorite in direct
collision course with Elmore...

03:09.156 --> 03:11.259
So there's some space
scientist outside.

03:11.292 --> 03:13.761
Big deal. We just wait
until our brains tune it out.

03:13.794 --> 03:16.297
You need
to leave your home --

03:16.330 --> 03:18.098
So there's a meteorite
in the living room.

03:18.131 --> 03:22.270
Big deal. We just wait
until our brains tune it out.

03:22.303 --> 03:24.672
[ Groaning ]
[ Bird caws ]

03:24.705 --> 03:27.841
So there's a bit of a virus
going around. Big deal.

03:27.875 --> 03:30.878
We just wait until
our brains tune it out.

03:30.911 --> 03:33.247
So people have six legs now.
Big deal.

03:33.281 --> 03:35.616
We just wait until
our brains tune it out.

03:35.649 --> 03:37.818
It may seem this is
the end for our kind,

03:37.851 --> 03:39.820
but your blood
may contain the key --

03:39.853 --> 03:45.025
♪♪

03:45.058 --> 03:46.560
The princess is ready
for her wedding.

03:46.594 --> 03:50.864
How does it feel to be married
to a wife from another planet?

03:50.898 --> 03:53.200
See, it simply went away.

03:53.233 --> 03:54.435
Who the who is that?

03:54.468 --> 03:56.737
[ Chanting ]
Ito maki maki, ito maki maki,

03:56.770 --> 03:59.607
ito ito, ton ton ton.

03:59.640 --> 04:01.275
I think we should stop
tuning things out.

04:01.309 --> 04:03.176
I'm kind of losing
the plot here.

04:03.210 --> 04:05.513
Meh.

04:05.546 --> 04:07.281
You're not gonna ask me
how I got here?

04:07.315 --> 04:09.182
Mm...nah.

04:09.216 --> 04:13.354
Announcer: [ On TV ]
Coming up next, Robot Dinosaur
Destruction Derby...

04:13.387 --> 04:14.822
Both: Yay.
...has been replaced
by a documentary

04:14.855 --> 04:16.790
about the Swedish
sheet metal industry.

04:16.824 --> 04:17.858
-Ugh.
-Ugh.

04:17.891 --> 04:20.494
Narrator: Gothenburg, 1953.

04:20.528 --> 04:22.496
[ Train horn blows ]

04:22.530 --> 04:24.765
[ Narrator continues
speaking indistinctly ]

04:24.798 --> 04:25.899
[ Men exclaiming ]

04:25.933 --> 04:28.936
[ Gumball grunting ]

04:28.969 --> 04:30.904
[ Creak! Wham! ]

04:30.938 --> 04:32.039
You know what?
Forget it.

04:32.072 --> 04:33.407
[ Sighs ]
Maybe there'll be

04:33.441 --> 04:35.309
a cool accident
at the sheet metal factory.

04:35.343 --> 04:37.378
And their factories
are the safest in the world.

04:37.411 --> 04:38.178
[ Both sigh ]

04:38.211 --> 04:40.080
[ Cellphone rings, both sigh ]

04:40.113 --> 04:42.983
What?
Ghost: [ Deep voice ]
Do you want to play a game?

04:43.016 --> 04:44.217
Oh, sure, I got a game!

04:44.251 --> 04:46.387
-And how do we play?
-Like this.

04:46.420 --> 04:47.855
Aw, man,
why is the universe

04:47.888 --> 04:49.457
so determined
to make us move today?

04:49.490 --> 04:50.924
Wouldn't its time
be better spent

04:50.958 --> 04:52.626
sorting out poverty
or world hunger

04:52.660 --> 04:54.995
or those awful
dog filters on Chat-Snap?

04:55.028 --> 04:57.030
[ Cellphone rings ]
What now?

04:57.064 --> 04:59.900
The game is on. I'm here.

04:59.933 --> 05:01.469
Then why are you
calling me?!

05:01.502 --> 05:03.537
[ Static ]

05:03.571 --> 05:11.044
♪♪

05:11.078 --> 05:12.312
-Ugh.
-Ugh.

05:12.346 --> 05:14.582
Really?
You gonna do me like that?

05:14.615 --> 05:16.950
Ugh, can we just
not do this right now?

05:16.984 --> 05:19.420
Do you know how long it took
to do my hair?

05:19.453 --> 05:21.955
What, you think it's easy
to look like this?

05:21.989 --> 05:23.424
You didn't even look at it.

05:23.457 --> 05:25.659
[ Sighs ]

05:25.693 --> 05:29.863
Do you even want to know
what's in the box?

05:29.897 --> 05:32.099
[ Sighs ]
Wow.

05:32.132 --> 05:36.203
Okay.
I think I'm gonna go.

05:36.236 --> 05:38.839
It was a cursed teddy bear
with human teeth.

05:38.872 --> 05:41.509
It was gonna creep closer to you
every time you looked away.

05:41.542 --> 05:44.311
Mm, wow. Th-That sounds
really scary.

05:44.344 --> 05:47.014
Don't! The surprise
is ruined now.

05:47.047 --> 05:48.682
-Ugh. W-Wait up!
-Yes?

05:48.716 --> 05:50.518
Pass us the remote
before you go, yeah?

05:50.551 --> 05:53.487
[ Sighs ]

05:53.521 --> 05:54.855
Just one last thing
before I --

05:54.888 --> 05:58.191
[ Upbeat music playing loudly
on TV ]

05:58.225 --> 05:59.427
You can go, too,
by the way.

05:59.460 --> 06:03.997
Okay. Hyah-ee!
Teleportation!

06:04.031 --> 06:06.366
[ Doorbell rings ]
Ah! Burrito delivery!

06:06.400 --> 06:08.802
I thought we weren't getting up.
No need to.

06:08.836 --> 06:11.939
Uh, hey! Can you post the
burritos through the mail slot?

06:11.972 --> 06:14.508
Larry: What?
Ugh. W-What part of that
didn't make sense?

06:14.542 --> 06:17.044
Everything from "post"
to "slot," if I'm honest,

06:17.077 --> 06:19.146
but the customer's
always right, I guess.

06:19.179 --> 06:21.381
♪♪

06:21.415 --> 06:24.084
Did you bring
the extra guac?

06:24.117 --> 06:26.820
Okay, now feed your hands
through the mail slot.

06:26.854 --> 06:30.157
What? Why?
Do you want your tip
or not, dude?

06:30.190 --> 06:32.993
'Kay, there's a shovel
to your left. Grab it.

06:33.026 --> 06:34.294
[ Grunts ]

06:34.327 --> 06:36.697
Now use it to flip
the burritos towards us.

06:36.730 --> 06:39.166
What? That's crazy.
I didn't sign up for this.

06:39.199 --> 06:40.534
It says on your website
that you deliver

06:40.568 --> 06:42.536
directly to us
in under 20 minutes,

06:42.570 --> 06:44.872
and the clock
is ticking, man.

06:44.905 --> 06:46.707
Eh, okay, okay.
[ Grunting ]

06:46.740 --> 06:49.843
No, no, wrong end
of the shovel.

06:49.877 --> 06:51.445
No, wrong direction.

06:51.479 --> 06:53.514
Come on, buddy,
time's running out.

06:55.549 --> 06:58.151
[ Grunts ]

06:58.185 --> 07:00.688
Mm-kay, now hold out
the shovel for your tip.

07:03.691 --> 07:04.925
There's nothing here.

07:04.958 --> 07:06.727
Eh, just keep
the shovel, then.

07:06.760 --> 07:09.362
Darn kids never
appreciate anything.

07:09.396 --> 07:11.198
[ Thunder crashes ]

07:12.666 --> 07:15.503
[ Groans ]
Are you calling
the TV repairman?

07:15.536 --> 07:17.471
Nah, I'm video-calling
Banana Joe.

07:17.505 --> 07:19.607
Hey, man! Thanks for calling.
Want to hang out?

07:19.640 --> 07:20.974
-No.
-Oh.

07:21.008 --> 07:23.176
-Then what can I do for you?
-Turn your phone to the TV.

07:23.210 --> 07:24.645
Okay. Anything else?

07:24.678 --> 07:26.179
Yeah, stop talking.
I'm trying to listen.

07:26.213 --> 07:29.182
Okay.
[ Wheezing quietly ]

07:29.216 --> 07:30.518
Yeah, and could you
stop breathing, please?

07:30.551 --> 07:32.185
-I can't hear.
-No problemo.

07:32.219 --> 07:35.355
[ Inhales deeply ]

07:35.388 --> 07:37.825
Ow.
What is going on here?

07:37.858 --> 07:40.360
♪♪

07:40.393 --> 07:43.430
All right, universe!
Bring it on!

07:43.463 --> 07:44.665
[ Electricity crackles ]

07:44.698 --> 07:46.266
[ Dinging ]

07:46.299 --> 07:48.636
Okay, maybe we need to
at least deal with that.

07:48.669 --> 07:49.870
Eh, in a minute.

07:51.972 --> 07:54.575
-You said you'd deal with it.
-I said I'd do it in a minute.

07:54.608 --> 07:56.309
You don't have to
remind me every hour.

07:56.343 --> 07:57.511
I think I'm gonna pass out.

07:57.545 --> 07:59.713
Oh, good idea!
Just lie down flatter.

07:59.747 --> 08:01.815
Uh, heat goes up, right?

08:01.849 --> 08:04.618
We interrupt this
with some breaking news.

08:04.652 --> 08:06.153
The police and fire departments

08:06.186 --> 08:08.188
are desperately trying
to rescue a family

08:08.221 --> 08:10.558
who crashed their car
on a freeway bridge.

08:10.591 --> 08:12.593
The authorities are unable
to approach the vehicle

08:12.626 --> 08:14.762
due to the bridge's
extreme instability.

08:14.795 --> 08:17.598
However, they say it may be able
to support a lighter weight

08:17.631 --> 08:20.000
such as one, maybe two,
12-year-old boys.

08:20.033 --> 08:22.636
[ All scream ]
Come on, Darwin, we got to go!

08:22.670 --> 08:25.839
[ All sigh ]
Uh, wait. Maybe not.

08:25.873 --> 08:28.075
[ All scream ]
Oh, no, we do have to go!

08:28.108 --> 08:30.143
[ All sigh ]
Or maybe not.

08:30.177 --> 08:31.278
[ All scream ]

08:31.311 --> 08:32.379
[ All sigh ]

08:32.412 --> 08:34.181
[ All scream, sigh ]

08:34.214 --> 08:36.784
[ Screaming, sighing ]

08:36.817 --> 08:38.986
All right, all right,
we're going! Man.

08:39.019 --> 08:42.055
[ Door opens, shuts ]

08:42.089 --> 08:43.190
[ Gasps ]

08:43.223 --> 08:45.292
[ Feet pattering ]

08:48.128 --> 08:51.098
[ Blowers whirring ]

08:51.131 --> 08:53.166
Are you thinking
what I'm thinking?

08:53.200 --> 08:54.802
Yes. It'd be
far too much effort

08:54.835 --> 08:56.837
to make the detour
to get those leaf blowers.

08:56.870 --> 08:59.306
Exactly.

08:59.339 --> 09:01.842
Wait, I've got a better idea.
We got wheels!

09:01.875 --> 09:04.177
We just have to stop and let
the rotation of the earth

09:04.211 --> 09:05.913
do the leg work for us.

09:05.946 --> 09:09.783
♪♪

09:09.817 --> 09:12.219
All right, let's just
call the cab company.

09:12.252 --> 09:15.388
[ All scream ]
[ Cellphone ringing ]

09:15.422 --> 09:18.325
Hello? Gumball? What do you mean
you need a ride?

09:18.358 --> 09:20.694
I'm dangling off a bridge here.
No, I can't.

09:20.728 --> 09:22.796
No, Dad can't, either.
We're stuck here in mortal d--

09:22.830 --> 09:25.365
Look, I don't have time
for this.

09:25.398 --> 09:27.334
[ Cellphone rings ]
Hello?

09:27.367 --> 09:29.436
Yeah, sure I can.
What time?

09:29.469 --> 09:31.538
Uh, I mean your mom
already said no, goodbye.

09:31.571 --> 09:32.873
[ Sighs ]
No dice.

09:32.906 --> 09:35.275
Oh, I got an idea.
[ Cellphone chimes ]

09:35.308 --> 09:37.077
"Your order is being
delivered --"

09:37.110 --> 09:38.779
Did anyone order anything?

09:38.812 --> 09:40.781
Gumball: You mind moving forward
a little?

09:40.814 --> 09:42.616
A little more.

09:42.650 --> 09:44.618
Little more.

09:44.652 --> 09:46.887
Little more.

09:46.920 --> 09:48.421
Okay, perfect.

09:48.455 --> 09:50.858
-That'll be $35!
-What?!

09:50.891 --> 09:54.361
Sorry, we couldn't be bothered
to buy stamps, so we improvised.

09:54.394 --> 09:57.965
[ Sighs ] Can you just
help us out, please?

09:57.998 --> 09:59.566
And here's your change.

09:59.599 --> 10:01.268
[ Ting! ]

10:01.301 --> 10:03.270
[ All screaming ]

10:03.303 --> 10:05.138
[ Gasps ]
I'm coming!

10:05.172 --> 10:09.509
♪♪

10:09.542 --> 10:10.911
They're not
gonna make it!

10:10.944 --> 10:13.280
We're gonna have to
get up from our chairs.

10:13.313 --> 10:15.215
Not on my day off.

10:15.248 --> 10:24.391
♪♪

10:24.424 --> 10:27.227
[ Slow-motion sighing ]

10:27.260 --> 10:28.829
[ Sighs ]

10:28.862 --> 10:30.497
Gumball, you did it.

10:30.530 --> 10:32.900
-Come here, son.
-Nah, you come here.

10:32.933 --> 10:34.067
-Ugh.
-Ugh.

10:34.101 --> 10:37.104
[ Yawns ] So, what's left
on our to-do list?

10:37.137 --> 10:38.872
-Nuttin'.
-Well, I guess

10:38.906 --> 10:40.307
we better get on with it.

10:40.340 --> 10:42.776
[ Both scream ]

10:42.810 --> 10:44.778
"This is a message
from the future.

10:44.812 --> 10:48.181
The strange things that happened
today were for a reason.

10:48.215 --> 10:50.417
And it was all
the work of..."

10:50.450 --> 10:52.085
Oh, my gosh. Darwin.

10:52.119 --> 10:53.787
Who could be sending
that message?

10:53.821 --> 10:55.588
No, I mean I just
found couch candy!

10:55.622 --> 10:57.457
-Whoo-hoo!
-Whoa!

10:57.490 --> 11:01.695
[ Both sigh ]
[ Upbeat music plays on TV ]

11:02.796 --> 11:11.104
♪♪

11:11.138 --> 11:19.312
♪♪

11:19.346 --> 11:27.454
♪♪

11:27.487 --> 11:35.896
♪♪
